      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WILLOWS GIRL (8) has been freshened since her last-start seventh in the NSW Oaks but had won four in a row prior, highlighted by the Gold Bracelet at Bathurst. Draws widest but has the class edge on this field. EYE WISH (5) deserved the last-start Albury win after placing in her first three starts off a spell including a 3.6m third to WILLOWS GIRL in the Gold Bracelet. Draws inside that rival and goes very well here with two wins and a placing from three attempts. DEVIOUS MINDS (2) was held up last start but draws well and did manage to overcome a second line barrier for a Penrith win last month. CAPTAINS DELIGHT (1) added to a string of top-two finishes when she came from the back row for a 1.8m second at Menangle last start. Drew wider than this when she scored at Penrith prior and draws for a soft run.",
